  "name": "mysqlite_upsert",
  "notes": "Hybrid of MySQL's backtick identifiers and hash comments with SQLite's type-affinity philosophy and Snowflake's MERGE-style UPSERT keyword. The at-sign wildcard (@) replaces the usual star for SELECT ALL columns, creating a visually distinct surface. EXCEPT and INTERSECT bind tighter than UNION (reversed precedence from standard SQL). Division by zero returns NULL (MySQL-like). LIKE is case-sensitive (SQLite-with-binary-collation style). Lowercase identifier fold with case-sensitive quoted identifiers.",
